				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Today in Small Business: Minimum Wage and Marijuana</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Gene Marks			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-11-04T17:05:27+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">November 4, 2014 12:05 pm</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">November 4, 2014 12:05 pm</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/11/04/today-in-small-business-minimum-wage-and-marijuana/" data-title="Today in Small Business: Minimum Wage and Marijuana" data-description=" Why the economy and voter perception of the economy are two different things. A study shows that shorter email subject lines deliver higher open rates. Is it possible to go an entire week using only mobile payment?">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>The Elections</strong></p>
<ul>
<ul>
<li>Why the economy and <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/11/04/upshot/the-economy-and-voters-perception-of-it-are-two-very-different-things.html">voter perception of the economy</a> are two different things.</li>
<li>John Oliver says <a href="//www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/wonkblog/wp/2014/11/03/wonkbook-john-oliver-is-right-state-level-elections-are-what-matters-on-tuesday/">the only thing</a> that matters are state-level elections.</li>
<li>Voters in five states are deciding whether to <a href="//www.vox.com/2014/11/4/7150509/minimum-wage-ballot-measures-2014-midterm-elections">increase their minimum wage</a>.</li>
<li>Here&#8217;s <a href="//www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/wonkblog/wp/2014/11/03/these-four-states-will-write-the-next-chapter-of-marijuana-reform-on-election-day/">how marijuana will fare</a> in the election.</li>
<li>We just spent <a href="//www.cnn.com/2014/11/01/politics/4-billion-expensive-election/">$4 billion on the midterms</a> &#8212; about what Apple spent on advertising over the last four years.</li>
</ul>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span id="more-89876"></span></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>The Economy</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A popular manufacturing index reports its <a href="//www.economicpopulist.org/content/ism-manufacturing-shows-highest-production-decade-and-new-orders-fire-5598">highest production</a> in a decade.</li>
<li>Oil <a href="//www.foxbusiness.com/markets/markets/2014/11/03/oil-closes-below-7-barrel/">closes below</a> $79 a barrel.</li>
<li>Small business <a href="//www.cnbc.com/id/102145182?trknav=homestack:topnews:8">borrowing is the highest</a> in seven-and-a-half years.</li>
<li>The <a href="//blogs.wsj.com/moneybeat/2014/11/03/dollar-bets-hit-fresh-record-with-no-sign-of-slowdown/">dollar</a> continues its blistering run.</li>
<li>The share of first-time <a href="//blogs.wsj.com/economics/2014/11/03/share-of-first-time-home-buyers-hits-27-year-low/?m">home buyers</a> hits a 27-year low.</li>
<li>Construction <a href="//www.bakersfieldnow.com/news/business/US-construction-spending-down-for-second-month-281337961.html">spending fell</a> for a second straight month in September.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Cash Flow</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>PayPal <a href="//venturebeat.com/2014/11/03/paypal-officially-launches-pay-after-delivery-service-announces-order-ahead-for-u-s-burger-king-locations/">releases</a> a new service that will allow users to pay for their goods up to 14 days after they make a purchase.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Employees</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Monster is trying to restore its <a href="//bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/11/02/a-faded-monster-seeks-a-return-to-glory/">faded job-search brand</a>.</li>
<li>Hereâs some advice on how to choose <a href="//runapptivo.apptivo.com/how-to-choose-the-right-employees-for-your-business-12325.html">the right employees</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Health Care</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A survey finds that 51 percent of <a href="//www.cnbc.com/id/102142296">people who used</a> government-run health insurance exchanges in the last year say they will not to do so again.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Entrepreneurship</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Recently divorced and jobless, a <a href="//www.inc.com/will-yakowicz/hotcakes-bakes-elfie-weiss.html">maker of cupcakes</a> risked her home and financial stability to achieve success.</li>
<li>Veteran entrepreneurs are <a href="//www.abc3340.com/story/27196024/veteran-entrepreneurs-honored-during-national-veterans-small-business-week-nov-3-7#.">honored during</a> National Veterans Small Business Week.</li>
<li>Why <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/11/04/opinion/space-tourism-isnt-frivolous-or-impossible.html">private space travel</a> is neither frivolous nor impossible.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Marketing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A study shows that shorter <a href="//www.dexmedia.com/blog/study-shows-shorter-email-subject-lines-deliver-higher-open-rates/">email subject lines</a> deliver higher open rates.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Management</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Here is how a <a href="//www.forbes.com/sites/capitalonespark/2014/11/03/how-a-third-generation-family-business-keeps-customers-coming-back/">third-generation family business</a> keeps its customers coming back.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the Country</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The <a href="//www.cnbc.com/id/102146596">World Trade Center</a> reopens after 13 years.</li>
<li>A Chocolate Expo <a href="//www.northjersey.com/news/chocolate-expo-draws-thousands-to-secaucus-1.1124998">draws thousands</a> to Secaucus, N.J.</li>
<li>A small business owner inÂ New Jersey <a href="//www.app.com/story/money/business/questions-and-answers/2014/11/03/shore-cake-supply/17724267/">sells cake and candy supplies</a> to bakers of all skill levels and ages.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the World</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The Economist measures <a href="//www.economist.com/blogs/economist-explains/2014/11/economist-explains-1?fsrc=scn/tw/te/bl/ee/costoftrafficjams">the cost of traffic jams</a>.</li>
<li>Germany <a href="https://gigaom.com/2014/11/03/germany-weighs-law-that-could-mean-more-trouble-for-u-s-tech-heavyweights/">weighs a law</a> that could mean more trouble for American tech companies.</li>
<li>Norway is the world&#8217;s <a href="//www.thelocal.no/20141103/norway-is-worlds-most-prosperous-country">most prosperous</a> country, and Singapore <a href="//money.cnn.com/2014/11/03/news/economy/singapore-best-business/index.html">tops a list</a> of best places to do business.</li>
<li>Indiaâs <a href="//news.yahoo.com/india-factory-output-rises-october-survey-081500132.html?s">factory output</a> rose in October.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Online</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Bank of Americaâs <a href="//consumerist.com/2014/11/03/bank-of-america-says-online-banking-has-been-restored-after-outage/">online banking</a> service suffers an outage.</li>
<li>Here are 24 <a href="//www.clearskyseo.com/24-eye-popping-seo-statistics-infographic/">eye-popping</a> search engine optimization statistics.</li>
<li>Online sales revenue is <a href="//www.cnbc.com/id/102146415">expected to reach</a> a record high during November and December (but the rate of growth will slow).</li>
<li>This is how one hotel <a href="//www.forbes.com/sites/jaysondemers/2014/11/03/how-one-hotel-ruined-its-reputation-by-penalizing-negative-reviews/">hurt its reputation</a> by penalizing negative reviews.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Opportunities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Edible insects are a <a href="//www.fastcompany.com/3037716/inside-the-edible-insect-industrial-complex">$20 million industry</a>, complete with consultants.</li>
<li>Smartphone and tablet repairs <a href="//www.telegram.com/article/20141103/NEWS/311039864/1101/newsrewind">are becoming a booming</a> business.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Technology</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Starwood Hotels &amp; Resorts <a href="//www.hospitalitynet.org/news/4067613.html">introduces</a> a mobile, keyless, room-entry system.</li>
<li>Is it possible to go an entire week <a href="//www.marketplace.org/topics/tech/living-without-cash-or-credit-cards-week#.VFjNrGUBlF8.twitter">using only mobile payment</a>?</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><em>Gene Marks owns the <a href="//www.marksgroup.net">Marks Group</a>, a Bala Cynwyd, Pa., consulting firm that helps clients with customer relationship management. You can follow him on <a href="https://www.twitter.com/genemarks">Twitter</a>.</em></p>
<div id="addendums" class="addendums"><div class="story-addendum theme-correction"><strong>Correction: November 4, 2014</strong> <br>An earlier version of this post misstated the status of a maker of cupcakes who risked her home and financial stability to achieve success. She was divorced and jobless, not divorced and childless.</div></div>	</div>
